01/08/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- US Ambassador-at-Large for War Crimes Issues Clint Williamson says Croatia's co-operation with the International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia sets a good example for Serbia and other countries in the region.
During a meeting with President Stipe Mesic in Zagreb on Monday (31 July), Williamson praised Croatian authorities for their courage in resolving outstanding issues with the UN tribunal, particularly the case of top indictee Ante Gotovina.
The US envoy is making a regional tour that includes stops in Belgrade, Sarajevo and Banja Luka.
(Poslovni dnevnik, Vjesnik - 01/08/06)
